{"lemma":"تَمامٌ","slug":"تَمامٌ","root":"ت.م.م","root_slug":"ت-م-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ت-م-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"تَمام","root":"تمم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n4091","n4092","n4093"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D9%8E%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of تَمَّ (tamma) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"completeness, wholeness, entirety"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"perfection"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"complete, whole, entire, full"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"perfect","tags":["perfect"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"separate, independent"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of تَمَّ (tamma) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of تَمَّ (tamma) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Cognate with Hebrew תָּמִים (tamím)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n4091","headword_ar":"تَمَامٌ","root":"tm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"timaAmN","text_ar":"تِمَامٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tumaAmN","text_ar":"تُمَامٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) inf. ns. of 1, in the first of the senses explained above; (T, S, M, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tim~N","text_ar":"تِمٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tam~N","text_ar":"تَمٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tum~N","text_ar":"تُمٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K.) [Hence,] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waladatohu litim~K","text_ar":"وَلَدَتْهُ لِتِمٍّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"litimaAmK","text_ar":"لِتِمَامٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"litamaAmK","text_ar":"لِتَمَامٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She brought him forth at the completion of formation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when his formation was complete:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at the completion of gestation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and, accord. to As,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waladatohu Alt~amaAma","text_ar":"وَلَدَتْهُ التَّمَامَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with the art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":"; not indeterminate, except in poetry. (IB, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waladato","text_ar":"وَلَدَتْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"litamaAmK","text_ar":"لِتَمَامٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"litimaAmK","text_ar":"لِتِمَامٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She brought forth at the completion of formation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of gestation"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloqati Alwalada ligayori tamaAmK","text_ar":"اَلْقَتِ الوَلَدَ لِغَيْرِ تَمَامٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"timaAmK","text_ar":"تِمَامٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She cast the child at a period not that of the completion of formation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of gestation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prematurely"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wulida Almawoluwdu litamaAmK","text_ar":"وُلِدَ المَوْلُودُ لِتَمَامٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"litimaAmK","text_ar":"لِتِمَامٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The infant was born at the completion of formation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of gestation"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T, * S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wulida Alwaladu litamaAmi","text_ar":"وُلِدَ الوَلَدُ لِتَمَامِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHamoli","text_ar":"الحَمْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHamoli","text_ar":"الحَمْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"litimaAmi","text_ar":"لِتِمَامِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The child was born at the completion of gestation"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) [These exs., and others following, show that an assertion of IDrd, mentioned in the M, namely, that one says, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wulida AlgulaAmu litim~K","text_ar":"وُلِدَ الغُلَامُ لِتِمٍّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"litimaAmK","text_ar":"لِتِمَامٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badoru timaAmK","text_ar":"بَدْرُ تِمَامٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and that in every other case it is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamaAm","text_ar":"تَمَام"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h, requires consideration.] You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badoru tamaAmK","text_ar":"بَدْرُ تَمَامٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"timaAmK","text_ar":"تِمَامٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The full moon of completion"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badorN timaAmN","text_ar":"بَدْرٌ تِمَامٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A complete full moon"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: all meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the moon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a moon, when it is full, so that it shines brightly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qamarN tamaAmN","text_ar":"قَمَرٌ تَمَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"timaAmN","text_ar":"تِمَامٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A complete,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"full, moon."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolapu Alt~amaAmi","text_ar":"لَيْلَةُ التَّمَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolapu tamaAmi Alqamari","text_ar":"لَيْلَةُ تَمَامِ القَمَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":", (ISh, T,) or ↓,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laylapu Alt~imaAmi","text_ar":"لَيلَةُ التِّمَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"with kesr, [which seems to be at variance with general usage,] and sometimes with fet-h, (Msb,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The night of the completion of the moon;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the night of the full moon;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, T, Msb;) which is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the thirteenth night;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, T;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the fourteenth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolu Alt~imaAmi","text_ar":"لَيْلُ التِّمَامِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr only, (T, S, M, K, &c.,) thus distinguished from what next precedes, (ISh, T,) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolu timaAmK","text_ar":"لَيْلُ تِمَامٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolN","text_ar":"لَيْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"timaAmN","text_ar":"تِمَامٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolN timaAmiY~N","text_ar":"لَيْلٌ تِمَامِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The longest night of the year;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the longest night of winter;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, ISh, T, M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that in which our Lord Jesus was born:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, T:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"each of three nights of which no deficiency is apparent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the night that is from thirteen to fifteen hours in length:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-'Amr EshSheybánee, T:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the night that is twelve hours or more in length:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, T, M, K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any night that is long,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tedious, to one, and in which one does not sleep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"is called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolapu Alt~imaAmi","text_ar":"لَيْلَةُ التِّمَامِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", or said to be like the night thus called. (IAar, T.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~ahori","text_ar":"الشَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruy^iYa AlhilaAlu litim~i","text_ar":"رُيِىَ الهِلَالُ لِتِمِّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The new moon was seen at the completion of the month;"},{"kind":"text","text":"showing that another month was commencing]. (T.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abaY qaAy^iluhaA A_il~aA tim~FA","text_ar":"اَبَى قَايِلُهَا اـِلَّا تِمًّا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tam~FA","text_ar":"تَمًّا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tum~FA","text_ar":"تُمًّا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M,) three dial. vars., of which the first is the most chaste, i. e.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamaAmFA","text_ar":"تَمَامًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sayer thereof refused,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"did not consent to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"aught"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"save completion"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he executed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accomplished,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kept to, his saying; he did not go back from it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamaAmN","text_ar":"تَمَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(with fet-h only, AZ, AAF, M) also signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"complement"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing; the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supplement"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof; the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing by the addition of which is effected the completion"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perfection"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing; (AZ, T, AAF, M, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamaAmapN","text_ar":"تَمَامَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tatim~apN","text_ar":"تَتِمَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, M, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*ihi Ald~araAhimu","text_ar":"هٰذِهِ الدَّرَاهِمُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamaAmu h`*ihi AlmiAy^api","text_ar":"تَمَامُ هٰذِهِ المِايَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h*h AlmAy^p","text_ar":"هذه الماية"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tatim~apu","text_ar":"تَتِمَّةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"These dirhems are the complement of this hundred;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what complete this hundred."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) [And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tatim~apu","text_ar":"تَتِمَّةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kitaAbK","text_ar":"كِتَابٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The supplement of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to, a book."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAm~N","text_ar":"تَامٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":["T","S","K","M","TA","ISh","Msb","As","Lth","AA"]},{"entry_id":"n4092","headword_ar":"تُمَامٌ","root":"tm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamaAmN","text_ar":"تَمَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n4093","headword_ar":"تِمَامٌ","root":"tm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamaAmN","text_ar":"تَمَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", throughout the greater part of the paragraph: ―         -b2-  and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAm~N","text_ar":"تَامٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}